																		IT&#039;S THE END OF THE WORLD AS WE KNOW IT
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1841781&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610221945" alt="A Random Day" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1841781)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;" >A Random Day</a></span> <span class="odate time_1524283333 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">21 Apr 2018 04:02</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3775816">
									

<p>That's right - the first team contest this site has had in over TWO YEARS!</p>
<p>Feel free to recruit people in this discussion thread.</p>
<p>Please direct any and all questions to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/procyonlotor" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(778357); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=778357&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1526949665" alt="ProcyonLotor" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=778357)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/procyonlotor" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(778357); return false;">ProcyonLotor</a></span> via PMs.</p>
<p>And let the hype&#8230; COMMENCE!</p>
<p><strong>RULES UPDATE:</strong> You may <strong>NOT</strong> use drafts that existed before the contest went up. All entries should have been created after the contest page went up.</p>
<p><strong>RULES UPDATE:</strong> The previous restriction on format screws and GoI Formats have been eased: SCP format screws are acceptable, while new GoI Formats may be created only if the GoI in question has no pre-existing formats.</p>
<p><strong>RULES UPDATE:</strong> While your team may still write as many articles for the contest as you wish, only the five highest-rated articles produced by your team will count for final scoring purposes. Furthermore, only the two highest-rated articles of each type (SCP,Tale,GoI Format) will qualify within the top five. This is to encourage quality over quantity and to encourage teams to branch out into tales and GoI Formats.</p>
<p><strong>RULES UPDATE:</strong> Teams may create hub pages for their work. However, hub pages will not count for scoring nor for the minimum article requirements. Furthermore, they cannot be put up until your team has posted the minimum required number of articles.</p>
<p><strong>RULES UPDATE:</strong> Substantially unfinished works that were started before the contest may be allowed in on a case-by-case basis, generally if they were under 50% complete.</p>
<p><strong>RULES UPDATE:</strong> SCP supplements such as separate exploration logs, experiment logs, revised versions, etc. will count as extra entries past the main four. For example, if you have one tale, one GoI Format, and two SCPs with two supplements each, the highest-rated of the four supplements will count as the fifth entry for voting purposes.</p>
<p>Banner created by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/zhange" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2938475); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2938475&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1526949665" alt="Zhange" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2938475)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/zhange" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2938475); return false;">Zhange</a></span>!</p>

							</div>

								
